WEBVTT

00:00:55.661 --> 00:00:58.247
NEULSAEM GENERAL HOSPITAL

00:01:01.125 --> 00:01:01.959
Syria?

00:02:08.484 --> 00:02:10.903
EPISODE 7

00:02:14.865 --> 00:02:16.742
Apparently,
Han Seol-ah was the first to call it in.

00:02:18.118 --> 00:02:19.995
She even gave a witness statement.

00:02:22.915 --> 00:02:24.166
I'll call you back.

00:02:29.880 --> 00:02:31.340
So you just happened to be there

00:02:31.423 --> 00:02:33.509
when the accident occurred?

00:02:35.719 --> 00:02:36.887
Is this a coincidence too?

00:02:40.057 --> 00:02:41.767
This is the footage from my dashcam.

00:02:43.727 --> 00:02:45.479
I see you've got an alibi this time too.

00:02:45.562 --> 00:02:47.439
Just to be clear,

00:02:48.023 --> 00:02:50.442
I'm giving you this
in case it helps with the investigation.

00:02:53.153 --> 00:02:54.238
Got nothing to hide, huh?

00:02:55.447 --> 00:02:56.865
We'll see what forensics says.

00:03:07.876 --> 00:03:10.087
MISSED CALL
SEOL-AH

00:03:20.055 --> 00:03:21.640
Captain, look at this.

00:03:24.351 --> 00:03:25.185
APPROVED TRANSACTIONS
DOMESTIC & INTERNATIONAL

00:03:25.269 --> 00:03:26.729
Do Eun-hye submitted this.

00:03:26.812 --> 00:03:28.731
They were together
at the time of the yacht accident.

00:03:28.814 --> 00:03:31.275
His family home and private studio
are in Cheongun,

00:03:31.358 --> 00:03:32.776
so he goes there every weekend.

00:03:32.860 --> 00:03:34.445
LIST OF EVIDENCE: RECEIPT
DAEYONGRU CHEONGUN BRANCH: AUGUST 17, 2025

00:03:38.282 --> 00:03:39.366
And he was here with us

00:03:39.992 --> 00:03:42.036
when Woo-seok's accident occurred.

00:03:43.120 --> 00:03:45.414
What if we're on the wrong track?

00:04:02.848 --> 00:04:04.266
What if there's another accomplice?

00:04:05.476 --> 00:04:06.602
What about Do Eun-hyuk?

00:04:07.519 --> 00:04:10.564
Han Seol-ah could've brought him
to every crime scene to create an alibi.

00:04:14.318 --> 00:04:16.445
Are you saying
someone else is behind all this?

00:04:27.706 --> 00:04:29.124
Are you a moron?

00:04:29.208 --> 00:04:31.502
Why would you repair someone else's yacht?

00:04:31.585 --> 00:04:33.128
Do you just follow her orders?

00:04:34.088 --> 00:04:36.298
What would you have done
if it weren't for me?

00:04:38.258 --> 00:04:39.301
Seriously?

00:04:39.384 --> 00:04:40.469
Hey!

00:05:04.952 --> 00:05:08.330
Jun-beom started volunteering
for OnWorld in college.

00:05:09.248 --> 00:05:11.208
Even though he came
from a well-off family,

00:05:11.291 --> 00:05:13.877
he really cared about the underprivileged.

00:05:13.961 --> 00:05:16.004
Did he also volunteer overseas?

00:05:16.922 --> 00:05:18.632
If it hadn't been
for that incident in Syria…

00:05:19.633 --> 00:05:20.634
Syria?

00:05:34.565 --> 00:05:36.525
That could've been you.

00:05:37.401 --> 00:05:38.569
I'm saying

00:05:39.069 --> 00:05:40.904
you could've died.

00:05:42.030 --> 00:05:43.407
Yet you still believe Han Seol-ah?

00:05:44.283 --> 00:05:45.242
INTENSIVE CARE UNIT

00:05:45.325 --> 00:05:47.202
Do you think she saved you or something?

00:05:48.620 --> 00:05:50.247
It's the same as the Kim Yun-ji case.

00:05:51.165 --> 00:05:54.042
Han Seol-ah is always at the crime scene
but has a solid alibi every time.

00:05:55.460 --> 00:05:56.712
So?

00:05:57.337 --> 00:05:58.422
You think it's a coincidence?

00:05:58.505 --> 00:06:00.299
Isn't it more likely
she has an accomplice?

00:06:07.598 --> 00:06:08.807
We've ruled out Do Eun-hyuk.

00:06:10.017 --> 00:06:12.519
He was at the station
at the time of the accident.

00:06:13.312 --> 00:06:14.188
I suppose…

00:06:15.564 --> 00:06:18.108
she seems capable of manipulating
anyone she wants.

00:06:20.027 --> 00:06:22.487
And it's possible
she may have two or more helpers.

00:06:27.618 --> 00:06:30.329
But what would she get out of killing me
or Lee Kwang-jin?

00:06:30.913 --> 00:06:31.747
Tell me.

00:06:32.581 --> 00:06:34.082
Maybe it's your fixation on her

00:06:34.166 --> 00:06:35.667
that's keeping you
from seeing other possibilities.

00:06:36.251 --> 00:06:38.337
What if the real culprit is someone else?

00:06:38.420 --> 00:06:41.632
Are you saying someone is out to kill
only Han Seol-ah's associates?

00:06:45.802 --> 00:06:48.722
There's more than just the burner phone,
isn't there?

00:06:54.061 --> 00:06:54.978
This accident happened

00:06:56.647 --> 00:06:58.315
while I was tracking down a suspect.

00:06:58.398 --> 00:06:59.441
Who?

00:07:00.609 --> 00:07:01.652
Paek Jun-beom.

00:07:03.070 --> 00:07:04.238
Why do you suspect him?

00:07:04.321 --> 00:07:07.199
He had wine sold exclusively
at Yoon Seung-jae's restaurant,

00:07:07.282 --> 00:07:09.868
and he was at the scene
the night Kim Yun-ji died.

00:07:12.079 --> 00:07:13.580
And that's not all.

00:07:15.165 --> 00:07:16.625
He was in Syria.

00:07:17.376 --> 00:07:18.210
Syria?

00:07:18.961 --> 00:07:20.295
Lee Su-ho died there.

00:07:21.338 --> 00:07:23.423
Are you saying they're connected somehow?

00:07:24.216 --> 00:07:25.926
Lee Su-ho was an OnWorld employee,

00:07:27.219 --> 00:07:29.054
and Paek Jun-beom
did volunteer work for them.

00:07:30.639 --> 00:07:33.100
The one person tied to all the deaths
around Han Seol-ah…

00:07:35.018 --> 00:07:36.186
is Paek Jun-beom.

00:07:40.649 --> 00:07:42.234
PAEK JUN-BEOM (35 YEARS OLD)
CEO OF YOUR HOME

00:07:44.611 --> 00:07:47.197
Someone with money, time, and the means.

00:07:48.782 --> 00:07:50.826
Someone confirmed to have had contact
with Kim Yun-ji that day.

00:07:58.583 --> 00:08:00.419
HWANG SUK-JI (37 YEARS OLD)
CAFE THIRD NIGHT, HAN SEOL-AH'S FRIEND

00:08:01.586 --> 00:08:02.796
An uninvited guest

00:08:02.879 --> 00:08:05.132
who slipped into Royal Auction
despite not being a VIP.

00:08:11.346 --> 00:08:13.015
Whose movements should we check first?

00:08:29.948 --> 00:08:32.159
You shouldn't be moving around.

00:08:34.369 --> 00:08:35.620
I'm okay.

00:08:38.373 --> 00:08:41.209
I'm more worried about Mr. Lee Kwang-jin.

00:08:46.048 --> 00:08:47.674
What brought you
to the scene of the accident?

00:08:53.680 --> 00:08:56.516
Do you remember anything at all?

00:09:05.025 --> 00:09:06.735
I got a hint from the painting.

00:09:17.412 --> 00:09:18.497
Syria…

00:09:25.545 --> 00:09:28.048
I gave Mr. Lee your message,

00:09:28.131 --> 00:09:29.758
but don't wait for a response.

00:09:30.592 --> 00:09:33.595
He said he has nothing to say to you.

00:09:34.805 --> 00:09:35.889
I'm sorry.

00:09:37.641 --> 00:09:39.476
When does he return from Laos?

00:09:40.852 --> 00:09:41.770
Actually,

00:09:42.354 --> 00:09:43.980
he's flying back tonight.

00:09:50.070 --> 00:09:52.697
I was on my way to the airport
to see Mr. Lee Kwang-jin

00:09:52.781 --> 00:09:54.408
when I saw your car.

00:10:00.080 --> 00:10:02.124
Then I saw the black car
that had been following us

00:10:02.207 --> 00:10:04.000
right on your tail.

00:10:23.270 --> 00:10:26.106
I had a bad feeling,
so I turned my car around.

00:10:56.428 --> 00:10:57.345
Woo-seok!

00:10:58.180 --> 00:10:59.097
Woo-seok!

00:11:14.529 --> 00:11:16.281
So you saved me.

00:11:17.365 --> 00:11:19.576
Anyone would've done the same.

00:11:24.581 --> 00:11:25.415
But…

00:11:28.126 --> 00:11:29.920
what was the culprit after?

00:11:30.962 --> 00:11:33.006
He was trying to silence Mr. Lee.

00:11:34.674 --> 00:11:35.592
Paek Jun-beom

00:11:36.968 --> 00:11:39.429
volunteered for OnWorld
since he was in college.

00:11:40.013 --> 00:11:42.057
And I think
he was also with Lee Su-ho in Syria.

00:11:43.808 --> 00:11:44.976
An Orphan from Syria.

00:11:46.394 --> 00:11:48.063
He deliberately sent that painting.

00:11:50.065 --> 00:11:50.941
Probably.

00:11:51.525 --> 00:11:54.194
But why?

00:11:54.277 --> 00:11:57.572
If he and Su-ho were just colleagues,
he wouldn't have taken it this far.

00:11:57.656 --> 00:11:59.241
Mr. Lee Kwang-jin is the only one

00:12:00.367 --> 00:12:03.161
who could tell us why
Paek Jun-beom might've approached you.

00:12:04.913 --> 00:12:06.665
If he doesn't regain consciousness,

00:12:08.208 --> 00:12:09.543
then only Paek Jun-beom will know.

00:12:15.966 --> 00:12:18.969
NEULSAEM GENERAL HOSPITAL

00:12:22.514 --> 00:12:25.100
Stake out at the hospital
until Mr. Lee wakes up.

00:12:25.183 --> 00:12:26.017
Keep it discreet.

00:12:39.406 --> 00:12:40.824
My first official SIU mission.

00:12:40.907 --> 00:12:42.200
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE
SIU ASSISTANT MANAGER AHN YOUNG-SOO

00:12:43.577 --> 00:12:44.869
I'll make sure to see it through.

00:12:52.168 --> 00:12:53.962
VIOLENT CRIMES UNIT 1

00:12:56.590 --> 00:12:58.508
The dashcam analysis results are in.

00:13:06.474 --> 00:13:07.309
Look at this.

00:13:12.188 --> 00:13:13.815
This car caused the accident.

00:13:14.399 --> 00:13:16.693
Identifying the license plate
might take some time,

00:13:17.193 --> 00:13:18.445
but we've confirmed the model.

00:13:19.029 --> 00:13:20.322
Was the accident caught on camera?

00:13:21.615 --> 00:13:22.782
Here.

00:13:40.967 --> 00:13:42.385
She went to save him.

00:13:42.969 --> 00:13:44.846
It seems she really was a witness.

00:13:48.600 --> 00:13:50.810
PORTRAITS OF A WOMAN: SPECIAL EXHIBITION

00:13:52.979 --> 00:13:55.690
This time, we're opening the auction
with the emerging artists

00:13:55.774 --> 00:13:58.193
whose paintings drew intense bidding.

00:13:58.276 --> 00:14:00.612
The Stiller is scheduled as the 30th lot--

00:14:00.695 --> 00:14:03.365
Things will heat up immediately
if we go in this order.

00:14:04.157 --> 00:14:06.660
You really want to set the record
for the highest bid, don't you?

00:14:15.168 --> 00:14:16.169
Excuse me.

00:14:17.837 --> 00:14:18.922
Sir?

00:14:21.549 --> 00:14:23.093
Can I help you?

00:14:23.176 --> 00:14:24.052
Do you speak Spanish?

00:14:24.135 --> 00:14:25.553
Yes, just a little.

00:14:25.637 --> 00:14:26.680
Thank goodness.

00:14:27.347 --> 00:14:28.473
I like this painting.

00:14:29.349 --> 00:14:30.934
Is it possible to negotiate the price?

00:14:31.726 --> 00:14:34.604
You're a valued guest
who has traveled a long way,

00:14:34.688 --> 00:14:40.318
so of course, we can do that for you.

00:14:40.402 --> 00:14:41.403
Thank you.

00:14:41.486 --> 00:14:42.737
Thank you very much.

00:14:43.571 --> 00:14:45.907
He's going to purchase it,
so get it ready for him.

00:14:45.990 --> 00:14:47.075
Yes, ma'am.

00:14:48.993 --> 00:14:50.328
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

00:14:55.625 --> 00:14:58.628
Did you study art in Spain?

00:14:59.212 --> 00:15:02.215
When the company fired me
for selling a forgery,

00:15:03.800 --> 00:15:06.177
no one reached out to help me.

00:15:06.845 --> 00:15:09.013
So I packed my bags and got on a plane.

00:15:09.723 --> 00:15:11.224
I mopped the floors in the afternoon,

00:15:11.307 --> 00:15:13.393
and worked at a wine bar at night.

00:15:13.977 --> 00:15:16.563
The first thing I had to do to survive
was to learn the language.

00:15:16.646 --> 00:15:19.691
I'd listen closely,
then repeat it out loud.

00:15:20.483 --> 00:15:23.862
Learning the language helped me acquire
a few pieces of artwork,

00:15:24.446 --> 00:15:29.200
and that gave me the leverage I needed
to return to Royal Auction.

00:15:30.034 --> 00:15:31.619
That's how I survived.

00:15:32.912 --> 00:15:34.497
You're amazing, Chair Kim.

00:15:36.082 --> 00:15:39.252
To work your way back up
after losing everything…

00:15:39.961 --> 00:15:42.881
Most people who lose everything

00:15:43.965 --> 00:15:45.842
tend to give up.

00:15:47.677 --> 00:15:49.220
If you've lost everything,

00:15:49.929 --> 00:15:51.598
you've got nothing left to lose

00:15:53.016 --> 00:15:54.726
and nothing to fear.

00:16:12.702 --> 00:16:14.621
TAEMYUNG GROUP

00:16:17.081 --> 00:16:19.042
FIRE BREAKS OUT ON A TRUCK TRANSPORTING
TAEMYUNG CULTURAL FOUNDATION ART

00:16:19.125 --> 00:16:23.046
DAMAGE WORTH TENS OF BILLIONS OF WON,
NO CASUALTIES REPORTED

00:16:26.174 --> 00:16:28.760
Anyone at 1.5 billion?

00:16:34.182 --> 00:16:36.476
Vanished Sensation by Fabien Leclerc

00:16:36.559 --> 00:16:39.395
has been sold to Chairman Park Min-cheol
of Taemyung Group.

00:16:39.979 --> 00:16:41.564
Please give that to Chair Kim.

00:16:41.648 --> 00:16:44.567
This exhibition was only possible
thanks to her.

00:16:44.651 --> 00:16:47.195
He said the five lots he secured
during the special auction

00:16:47.278 --> 00:16:49.989
will be exhibited
at the Taemyung Art Center in Busan.

00:16:51.115 --> 00:16:52.450
Busan?

00:17:08.633 --> 00:17:10.927
PLEASE ENTER YOUR PASSWORD
TO UNLOCK THIS DRIVE

00:17:13.096 --> 00:17:15.932
TAEMYUNG GROUP AUCTION ARTWORK LIST

00:17:17.892 --> 00:17:19.185
VANISHED SENSATION,
THE REMAINS OF ECSTASY,

00:17:19.269 --> 00:17:20.228
THE ABYSS, ECHO, TURBULENCE

00:17:24.816 --> 00:17:29.571
GANGHA POLICE STATION

00:17:30.238 --> 00:17:31.906
According to the forensic results,

00:17:31.990 --> 00:17:33.950
the suspect's vehicle is a black sedan,
license plate ending in 4549.

00:17:34.826 --> 00:17:36.786
It's a ghost car with invalid plates.

00:17:39.414 --> 00:17:42.375
It crossed Yeongjong Bridge
and went toward Gangseo-gu.

00:17:42.458 --> 00:17:44.085
4549 MOVEMENT ROUTE

00:17:44.669 --> 00:17:46.546
When was it last caught on camera?

00:17:46.629 --> 00:17:47.839
Right here.

00:18:07.442 --> 00:18:08.484
I've seen him before.

00:18:23.374 --> 00:18:24.834
Flower delivery for Ms. Han Seol-ah.

00:18:25.793 --> 00:18:27.045
She's in there.

00:18:27.128 --> 00:18:28.087
Thank you.

00:18:30.256 --> 00:18:31.132
Flower delivery, ma'am.

00:18:35.345 --> 00:18:36.471
Who are they from?

00:18:36.554 --> 00:18:37.764
Just a moment.

00:18:38.598 --> 00:18:40.141
They were sent anonymously.

00:18:40.642 --> 00:18:41.476
Have a nice day.

00:18:53.863 --> 00:18:54.864
Happy birthday.

00:19:52.088 --> 00:19:53.047
My goodness.

00:19:53.131 --> 00:19:55.425
Mr. Cha isn't just good-looking.

00:19:55.508 --> 00:19:57.218
He's romantic as well.

00:19:57.760 --> 00:20:00.763
Ms. Han is so lucky
to have gotten a love confession.

00:20:01.347 --> 00:20:02.181
Love confession?

00:20:02.765 --> 00:20:03.725
Didn't you know?

00:20:03.808 --> 00:20:06.769
Lisianthus symbolizes eternal love.

00:20:09.063 --> 00:20:12.108
So, do you like flowers too?

00:20:13.192 --> 00:20:15.403
What woman doesn't like flowers?

00:21:05.661 --> 00:21:06.746
Seol-ah.

00:21:08.998 --> 00:21:10.083
You'd be happy…

00:21:13.044 --> 00:21:14.253
if I disappeared, right?

00:21:18.174 --> 00:21:19.050
That's…

00:21:22.053 --> 00:21:23.346
what you want, isn't it?

00:21:26.265 --> 00:21:28.226
I have no reason to live now.

00:21:30.186 --> 00:21:32.271
If dying is the only way
I can stay with you…

00:21:35.066 --> 00:21:35.983
I'll do it.

00:21:40.530 --> 00:21:42.031
I know I'm crazy.

00:21:43.825 --> 00:21:44.700
But…

00:21:45.827 --> 00:21:47.954
if it means you'll remember me forever…

00:21:51.207 --> 00:21:52.625
then I'll be the bad guy.

00:21:59.132 --> 00:22:00.341
You and I…

00:22:01.968 --> 00:22:03.386
have different goals.

00:22:05.847 --> 00:22:08.975
I barely got the internship
at Royal Auction.

00:22:09.058 --> 00:22:11.269
This opportunity is everything to me.

00:22:11.352 --> 00:22:14.438
So are you saying
I'm not worth a place in your life?

00:22:14.522 --> 00:22:15.731
Su-ho.

00:22:19.318 --> 00:22:20.736
Why won't you pick up? Who are you with?

00:22:20.820 --> 00:22:22.029
Why won't you answer my calls?!

00:22:22.572 --> 00:22:23.906
I'm working.

00:22:23.990 --> 00:22:24.949
You're…

00:22:25.032 --> 00:22:27.451
You're with that damn photographer,
aren't you?

00:22:27.535 --> 00:22:28.744
Stop already.

00:22:28.828 --> 00:22:30.371
So it's over
just because you want to break up?

00:22:30.454 --> 00:22:32.123
You're basically telling me to die.

00:22:32.582 --> 00:22:33.416
Yeah.

00:22:34.125 --> 00:22:36.544
Just die and stop bothering me!

00:22:36.627 --> 00:22:38.087
Is that what you really want?

00:22:38.963 --> 00:22:40.590
Do you even know what it means to die?

00:22:53.269 --> 00:22:54.187
Don't forget…

00:22:56.856 --> 00:22:57.732
that you're the one…

00:23:03.446 --> 00:23:04.655
who killed me.

00:23:36.437 --> 00:23:43.444
THE LATE LEE SU-HO
MAY 7, 1991 - JUNE 14, 2018

00:24:00.127 --> 00:24:02.255
FAITHFUL TO DUTY, FAITHFUL TO THE PEOPLE

00:24:02.338 --> 00:24:05.174
Captain thinks Paek Jun-beom
and Han Seol-ah conspired together.

00:24:06.050 --> 00:24:07.677
And I still suspect that Han Seol-ah

00:24:08.636 --> 00:24:10.554
was involved
in Kim Yun-ji's accident and yours.

00:24:11.806 --> 00:24:14.350
If we catch 4549,
we'll find out who's behind it.

00:24:15.017 --> 00:24:17.436
Fine, let's find the ghost car first

00:24:17.520 --> 00:24:18.854
and argue again later.

00:24:18.938 --> 00:24:20.523
How about we team up like old times?

00:24:20.606 --> 00:24:22.608
You cover the west side of Sanjun-dong,
and I'll cover the east side.

00:24:23.192 --> 00:24:24.026
All right.

00:25:30.801 --> 00:25:32.720
SANJUN JUNKYARD

00:25:50.279 --> 00:25:51.113
JUNKYARD

00:25:51.197 --> 00:25:52.114
Jeez, he's fast.

00:25:54.367 --> 00:25:55.785
I think it's that one over there.

00:25:59.413 --> 00:26:00.414
Hey.

00:26:01.290 --> 00:26:02.124
Hey.

00:26:29.443 --> 00:26:30.945
I only see trash.

00:26:35.533 --> 00:26:36.826
"Alpha Tower"?

00:26:37.410 --> 00:26:38.369
I think I know where he is.

00:26:40.204 --> 00:26:41.705
Call KCSI to collect the fingerprints.

00:26:41.789 --> 00:26:43.666
I'll try provoking Paek Jun-beom
a bit more.

00:26:51.424 --> 00:26:54.093
You're approaching your destination.
Ending navigation.

00:26:54.176 --> 00:26:56.011
ALPHA TOWER

00:27:03.561 --> 00:27:06.897
He's good-looking, tall, well-educated,

00:27:06.981 --> 00:27:08.983
and filthy rich from making an app.

00:27:09.608 --> 00:27:11.527
What brought you here

00:27:12.570 --> 00:27:13.863
at this particular time?

00:27:19.702 --> 00:27:23.330
YOUR HOME
CEO PAEK JUN-BEOM

00:28:01.118 --> 00:28:02.369
I'm Paek Jun-beom.

00:28:04.788 --> 00:28:06.916
Nice to meet you. I'm Paek Jun-beom.

00:28:07.583 --> 00:28:08.751
I see you're left-handed.

00:28:09.793 --> 00:28:12.171
Oh, I use it out of habit.

00:28:33.734 --> 00:28:35.110
Is this good enough?

00:28:38.113 --> 00:28:39.448
I've never really done this sort of thing.

00:28:40.658 --> 00:28:41.742
What's this?

00:28:43.035 --> 00:28:46.956
Well, I thought our plan was still on.

00:28:49.500 --> 00:28:50.334
Oh.

00:28:57.299 --> 00:28:58.342
You're right.

00:28:58.425 --> 00:29:00.844
In that case, I should react like this.

00:29:14.108 --> 00:29:15.192
Anyway,

00:29:15.276 --> 00:29:16.193
here you go.

00:29:16.902 --> 00:29:18.070
It's your birthday, after all.

00:29:19.488 --> 00:29:20.322
Thank you.

00:29:22.616 --> 00:29:23.492
Come on in.

00:29:34.420 --> 00:29:36.171
They were sent anonymously.

00:29:37.464 --> 00:29:40.009
They're the same flowers
Su-ho used to give me.

00:29:42.261 --> 00:29:44.054
How would he even know such a thing?

00:29:45.097 --> 00:29:48.142
I'm not sure how he knows…

00:29:50.019 --> 00:29:52.605
or what he wants from me.

00:29:54.398 --> 00:29:55.524
Was there any other message?

00:30:14.209 --> 00:30:15.794
It was written by a left-handed person.

00:30:17.004 --> 00:30:19.465
Mr. Paek is also left-handed.

00:30:29.058 --> 00:30:31.894
She always spends her birthday with us.

00:30:31.977 --> 00:30:33.020
Isn't this the first time she's done this?

00:30:34.396 --> 00:30:35.731
I'm a bit disappointed.

00:30:38.108 --> 00:30:40.235
Did you go all the way to Daejeon again
to get this?

00:30:40.319 --> 00:30:42.571
You go above and beyond, don't you?

00:30:42.655 --> 00:30:46.659
I'm a picky eater, but I'll never say no
to a strawberry tart.

00:30:47.534 --> 00:30:49.036
Yet you never get me one for my birthday.

00:30:50.621 --> 00:30:51.747
You can have it all.

00:30:53.123 --> 00:30:54.291
Really?

00:31:00.464 --> 00:31:01.757
Just look at the color.

00:31:08.347 --> 00:31:09.598
-Is it good?
-It's delicious.

00:31:11.975 --> 00:31:13.018
Cheers.

00:31:19.400 --> 00:31:21.819
We found it
thanks to your dashcam footage.

00:31:21.902 --> 00:31:23.028
It was a ghost car,

00:31:24.029 --> 00:31:26.281
and we tracked it entering and leaving
Your Home's office building.

00:31:28.325 --> 00:31:30.786
So Mr. Paek
definitely sent me the flowers.

00:31:40.629 --> 00:31:41.672
We have to do something.

00:31:49.054 --> 00:31:51.557
INSURANCE POLICY

00:31:56.395 --> 00:32:01.442
POLICYHOLDER: CHA WOO-SEOK
BENEFICIARY: HAN SEOL-AH

00:32:04.027 --> 00:32:06.530
If we set a trap,
he'll walk right into it.

00:32:09.158 --> 00:32:11.827
MAIN COVERAGE:
NATURAL DEATH, GENERAL INJURY

00:32:17.249 --> 00:32:18.292
Do I look like a joke?

00:32:19.543 --> 00:32:21.044
Why does everyone treat me as they wish?

00:32:22.629 --> 00:32:23.547
Seol-ah.

00:32:24.047 --> 00:32:25.674
You need to think about this rationally.

00:32:25.758 --> 00:32:27.593
The real culprit will show up
if we do this.

00:32:28.385 --> 00:32:31.346
Do you have any idea
how cruel this is to me?

00:32:32.222 --> 00:32:33.140
Seol-ah.

00:32:33.223 --> 00:32:35.642
What if I just use you and walk away?

00:32:38.061 --> 00:32:39.480
What if you really die?

00:32:45.736 --> 00:32:46.695
It doesn't matter.

00:32:48.822 --> 00:32:49.907
I don't care.

00:32:58.290 --> 00:32:59.458
Go ahead and use me.

00:33:03.128 --> 00:33:05.380
Have you ever lived with the guilt
of someone dying

00:33:05.464 --> 00:33:07.299
because of you?

00:33:08.801 --> 00:33:10.511
Do you know how painful that is?

00:33:15.516 --> 00:33:16.433
I do.

00:33:18.727 --> 00:33:20.229
I lost the only family I had.

00:33:29.154 --> 00:33:30.405
After our parents divorced…

00:33:32.366 --> 00:33:33.992
our grandmother raised us.

00:33:36.912 --> 00:33:38.455
After our grandmother passed away,

00:33:40.082 --> 00:33:41.208
it was just the two of us.

00:33:52.886 --> 00:33:56.473
The first thing I did when you told me
you were going to be a cop

00:33:56.557 --> 00:33:59.101
was to get a first aid kit.

00:34:01.728 --> 00:34:03.564
Please don't get hurt.

00:34:04.314 --> 00:34:07.985
I was supposed to be
Woo-hee's mom, dad, and older brother,

00:34:09.319 --> 00:34:10.821
but she took care of me instead.

00:34:12.030 --> 00:34:13.198
She was always strong.

00:34:13.282 --> 00:34:14.116
Even more so than me.

00:34:17.327 --> 00:34:18.370
After I became a cop,

00:34:20.247 --> 00:34:22.374
I spent day and night chasing criminals.

00:34:24.793 --> 00:34:26.587
But I couldn't protect my own family.

00:34:36.972 --> 00:34:39.600
If only I had just checked on her again,
I wouldn't have lost her that way.

00:34:47.441 --> 00:34:50.235
After I lost her, I threw myself
into solving cases like a madman.

00:34:50.944 --> 00:34:52.946
I thought working myself to death
and catching criminals

00:34:53.864 --> 00:34:55.699
would make me feel better.

00:34:57.868 --> 00:34:59.036
But it didn't.

00:35:00.454 --> 00:35:01.538
I realized…

00:35:03.582 --> 00:35:05.751
that no matter who I saved,
this guilt wouldn't go away.

00:35:07.753 --> 00:35:09.254
It wasn't your fault.

00:35:10.547 --> 00:35:11.423
No.

00:35:12.883 --> 00:35:14.176
It was my fault.

00:35:17.387 --> 00:35:18.931
I couldn't protect my sister.

00:35:25.771 --> 00:35:28.065
We're trapped in the same prison,

00:35:29.483 --> 00:35:31.109
living each day…

00:35:33.028 --> 00:35:34.446
with the people we couldn't protect.

00:35:49.586 --> 00:35:52.047
NEULSAEM GENERAL HOSPITAL

00:36:20.283 --> 00:36:21.284
You got me.

00:36:21.368 --> 00:36:22.953
I thought I was hiding it well.

00:36:23.662 --> 00:36:26.081
You need a good eye to be an auctioneer.

00:36:29.835 --> 00:36:31.336
Did you get hurt in the accident?

00:36:34.089 --> 00:36:35.007
Yes.

00:36:40.971 --> 00:36:42.055
From now on…

00:36:45.475 --> 00:36:46.601
please don't get hurt.

00:37:31.688 --> 00:37:32.898
AHN YOUNG-SOO

00:37:35.734 --> 00:37:36.568
I need to take this.

00:37:43.241 --> 00:37:44.951
-Hello?
-Mr. Cha.

00:37:45.035 --> 00:37:47.454
Mr. Lee Kwang-jin woke up.
They're moving him to a regular ward.

00:37:48.955 --> 00:37:50.040
Where are you right now?

00:37:51.041 --> 00:37:52.209
I'm in front of the ICU.

00:37:53.794 --> 00:37:55.003
Listen to me carefully.

00:38:00.258 --> 00:38:02.552
Mr. Lee regained consciousness.

00:38:03.929 --> 00:38:05.013
No, you stay here.

00:38:05.097 --> 00:38:06.264
It's better if we don't go together.

00:38:06.848 --> 00:38:08.266
We don't know what might happen.

00:38:08.350 --> 00:38:11.520
The police are suspicious of you,
and I don't want you to get in trouble.

00:38:13.814 --> 00:38:15.774
Okay, call me.

00:39:30.098 --> 00:39:35.061
LEE *****-JIN

00:42:10.884 --> 00:42:11.843
Are you sleeping?

00:42:13.011 --> 00:42:14.971
You should've followed him!

00:42:15.055 --> 00:42:17.349
Do you know how scary this was?

00:42:18.683 --> 00:42:20.643
Did you do as I said?

00:42:20.727 --> 00:42:21.686
Yes.

00:42:25.482 --> 00:42:26.858
Jeez, you scared me.

00:42:29.861 --> 00:42:31.071
What the…

00:42:37.118 --> 00:42:38.244
That little…

00:42:42.123 --> 00:42:43.416
This bastard is 4549.

00:42:43.500 --> 00:42:45.794
I knew I could do it!

00:42:48.505 --> 00:42:50.215
But he wasn't wearing a doctor's coat.

00:43:03.937 --> 00:43:04.938
No way.

00:43:24.791 --> 00:43:26.126
"Succinylcholine."

00:43:26.709 --> 00:43:28.503
What is that?

00:43:29.087 --> 00:43:30.755
An anesthetic used to put animals down.

00:43:31.423 --> 00:43:32.257
What?

00:43:32.841 --> 00:43:34.801
If it weren't for your foresight,

00:43:34.884 --> 00:43:37.262
Mr. Lee Kwang-jin
would've been in real danger.

00:43:38.138 --> 00:43:39.180
Where is he right now?

00:43:39.681 --> 00:43:41.057
Up there.

00:43:41.141 --> 00:43:42.016
Way up high.

00:43:45.103 --> 00:43:47.564
AHN *****-SOO

00:43:53.611 --> 00:43:55.071
Do you recognize him?

00:43:55.655 --> 00:43:57.115
Yes, that's Jun-beom.

00:44:19.512 --> 00:44:20.805
Were these taken in Syria?

00:44:23.016 --> 00:44:24.893
They were like brothers…

00:44:25.810 --> 00:44:27.228
before that accident.

00:44:28.980 --> 00:44:30.273
The whole refugee camp

00:44:30.815 --> 00:44:32.901
was completely destroyed
in the air strike that day.

00:44:33.776 --> 00:44:35.445
Su-ho died on the spot,

00:44:36.029 --> 00:44:38.698
and Jun-beom barely survived.

00:44:40.366 --> 00:44:42.285
After being brought to Korea for surgery,

00:44:42.368 --> 00:44:43.661
he vanished.

00:44:44.496 --> 00:44:46.956
What's Paek Jun-beom trying to hide?

00:44:47.999 --> 00:44:49.918
Are you sure he was behind this?

00:44:51.085 --> 00:44:52.003
Why would he?

00:44:54.339 --> 00:44:56.925
You know something important, don't you?

00:44:57.550 --> 00:45:00.011
Su-ho kept saying he wanted to die

00:45:00.094 --> 00:45:01.429
after his girlfriend broke up with him,

00:45:01.971 --> 00:45:03.640
and he even ignored the air raid warning.

00:45:04.933 --> 00:45:06.893
The way I see it,
he basically committed suicide.

00:45:10.897 --> 00:45:14.025
And Jun-beom got injured
trying to save Su-ho.

00:45:19.197 --> 00:45:22.492
YOUR HOME
CEO PAEK JUN-BEOM

00:46:29.434 --> 00:46:32.020
I found out where Lee Su-ho
was laid to rest.

00:46:33.646 --> 00:46:35.315
If it's too much for you to handle,
I'll come with you.

00:47:06.971 --> 00:47:09.307
THE LATE LEE SU-HO
MAY 7, 1991 - JUNE 14, 2018

00:47:20.068 --> 00:47:21.653
He was an orphan with no family,

00:47:22.528 --> 00:47:24.197
so I placed his ashes in a columbarium.

00:47:40.672 --> 00:47:41.506
I think

00:47:42.632 --> 00:47:44.676
Mr. Paek wanted me to come here.

00:47:49.222 --> 00:47:50.264
To be honest,

00:47:50.765 --> 00:47:53.810
I knew that Su-ho

00:47:55.019 --> 00:47:56.187
chose to end his life.

00:48:07.990 --> 00:48:08.908
Don't forget…

00:48:11.536 --> 00:48:12.578
that you're the one…

00:48:16.249 --> 00:48:17.542
who killed me.

00:48:23.381 --> 00:48:25.383
I couldn't bring myself to tell you

00:48:25.466 --> 00:48:26.968
because I was afraid you'd say

00:48:27.802 --> 00:48:29.721
I manipulated Su-ho into killing himself.

00:48:30.805 --> 00:48:32.140
What do you mean?

00:48:33.224 --> 00:48:35.518
I overheard what you said
to Detective Gong.

00:48:38.646 --> 00:48:41.023
She seems capable of manipulating
anyone she wants,

00:48:41.107 --> 00:48:43.526
and it's possible
she may have two or more helpers.

00:48:47.572 --> 00:48:49.532
You missed the rest of what I said.

00:48:49.615 --> 00:48:52.368
I only meant that's how detectives
might view things.

00:48:53.953 --> 00:48:54.912
You got it all wrong.

00:48:56.289 --> 00:48:58.291
I don't suspect you anymore.

00:48:58.374 --> 00:48:59.333
I believe you.

00:49:00.918 --> 00:49:03.337
That's why I'm telling you everything.

00:49:06.466 --> 00:49:10.344
He kept saying he was going to die,
so I just told him to die…

00:49:12.513 --> 00:49:14.015
and to stop bothering me.

00:49:15.516 --> 00:49:16.684
If only I hadn't said that

00:49:18.352 --> 00:49:19.937
on our last call…

00:49:20.480 --> 00:49:21.814
Don't blame yourself.

00:49:24.150 --> 00:49:25.943
It wasn't your fault.

00:49:28.279 --> 00:49:30.198
I think I know why he sent this.

00:49:31.574 --> 00:49:36.704
Mr. Paek is seeking revenge
on Su-ho's behalf.

00:49:38.623 --> 00:49:40.249
He's using every means possible

00:49:41.083 --> 00:49:42.919
to make me miserable.

00:49:48.341 --> 00:49:49.509
Since he gave you a gift,

00:49:51.177 --> 00:49:52.470
we should give him one in return.

00:49:58.684 --> 00:50:00.520
DNA MATCH
VEHICLE 4549, EVIDENCE IN ATTEMPTED MURDER

00:50:00.603 --> 00:50:02.438
The same DNA was collected

00:50:02.522 --> 00:50:04.482
from vehicle 4549 and the doctor's coat,

00:50:04.565 --> 00:50:05.900
and it matched with Kim Sung-hae,

00:50:05.983 --> 00:50:08.569
a 34-year-old man who had served time
for assault resulting in death.

00:50:08.653 --> 00:50:10.738
He's a former special forces NCO

00:50:11.322 --> 00:50:13.658
with service experience in Syria.

00:50:13.741 --> 00:50:16.285
He was in Syria with Paek Jun-beom, huh?

00:50:16.369 --> 00:50:18.996
That means Paek Jun-beom calls the shots,
and Kim Sung-hae just follows.

00:50:19.080 --> 00:50:20.790
But as of right now,

00:50:20.873 --> 00:50:23.626
his trips to the office building
aren't enough to tie him to the case

00:50:23.709 --> 00:50:25.628
unless a search and seizure is conducted.

00:50:25.711 --> 00:50:26.629
Let's catch them.

00:50:27.338 --> 00:50:30.049
Start with Kim Sung-hae.
Put out an APB for attempted murder.

00:50:31.259 --> 00:50:32.134
Yes, sir.

00:51:03.666 --> 00:51:04.500
Hello, Ms. Han.

00:51:04.584 --> 00:51:05.835
Allow me to escort you
to the CEO's office.

00:51:26.939 --> 00:51:28.357
Mr. Paek will be here soon.

00:51:28.441 --> 00:51:30.568
Please have a seat and wait for a moment.

00:51:30.651 --> 00:51:32.111
Sure thing.

00:51:37.950 --> 00:51:39.201
YOUR HOME
CEO PAEK JUN-BEOM

00:51:51.672 --> 00:51:52.590
DELETING…
SELECTED FILES: 30

00:51:52.673 --> 00:51:54.091
YOUR HOME INTEGRATED CONTROL CENTER
CCTV SYSTEM

00:51:54.175 --> 00:51:55.301
As instructed,

00:51:55.384 --> 00:51:58.137
we're deleting all the footage
tracking your movements, sir.

00:51:58.220 --> 00:52:00.890
Delete the recent footage
of the parking lot entrance too.

00:52:01.474 --> 00:52:02.600
All of it, sir?

00:52:04.477 --> 00:52:05.686
Understood.

00:52:07.104 --> 00:52:10.483
DELETING…
SELECTED FILES: 382

00:52:16.238 --> 00:52:18.824
The barrier gate camera
would've caught 4549

00:52:18.908 --> 00:52:21.452
as it entered and left
the office building.

00:52:22.578 --> 00:52:23.621
THANK YOU
GOODBYE

00:52:29.585 --> 00:52:30.795
Take a look at this, sir.

00:52:30.878 --> 00:52:34.340
This system automatically records
and recognizes license plates,

00:52:34.423 --> 00:52:36.550
but it also records who's inside the car.

00:52:37.718 --> 00:52:38.761
But the thing is,

00:52:38.844 --> 00:52:42.264
nobody thinks this is important,
so the security is pathetic.

00:52:42.348 --> 00:52:44.392
They might as well roll out a welcome mat.

00:52:44.475 --> 00:52:45.935
See? I'm in already.

00:52:46.018 --> 00:52:47.812
Grab all the files, then.

00:52:47.895 --> 00:52:49.188
Yes, sir.

00:52:50.982 --> 00:52:52.400
Right on it.

00:52:57.697 --> 00:52:58.531
THIS FILE HAS BEEN DELETED

00:52:58.614 --> 00:52:59.532
Hold on.

00:53:00.032 --> 00:53:02.827
These bastards are deleting
all the files in real time.

00:53:03.911 --> 00:53:06.372
They must've caught on
that we know about the ghost car.

00:53:07.123 --> 00:53:09.375
Paek Jun-beom isn't showing up
because he's busy deleting these files.

00:53:33.315 --> 00:53:35.234
HAN SEOL-AH

00:53:39.739 --> 00:53:42.033
I'm sorry. Something came up.

00:53:42.116 --> 00:53:43.492
Have you been waiting long?

00:53:43.576 --> 00:53:45.411
No, I just got here.

00:53:45.911 --> 00:53:46.871
Please sit.

00:53:51.625 --> 00:53:52.460
Here.

00:54:03.596 --> 00:54:05.139
YOU ARE CORDIALLY INVITED TO ROYAL AUCTION
KOREA'S PREMIER FINE ART AUCTION HOUSE

00:54:07.016 --> 00:54:07.933
An invitation?

00:54:08.893 --> 00:54:12.688
It's for a preview event
for our VVIP clients,

00:54:12.772 --> 00:54:16.650
and it'll also be the first public showing
of the Stiller.

00:54:17.234 --> 00:54:18.652
Then I should attend.

00:54:18.736 --> 00:54:20.071
That piece meant a great deal to me.

00:54:22.114 --> 00:54:24.658
Everyone has been wondering
who owned the Stiller.

00:54:26.285 --> 00:54:29.789
Are you okay with your identity
being revealed?

00:54:36.545 --> 00:54:38.047
I liked having an air of mystery,

00:54:38.130 --> 00:54:40.091
but I guess that's over now,
thanks to you.

00:54:42.218 --> 00:54:43.427
By the way,

00:54:44.512 --> 00:54:46.013
about An Orphan from Syria…

00:54:51.685 --> 00:54:54.688
That piece clearly means a lot to you.

00:54:57.233 --> 00:55:00.194
May I ask why you consigned it to me?

00:55:10.538 --> 00:55:13.207
I wanted to show more of myself.

00:55:15.126 --> 00:55:17.086
The piece feels like the real me
without a mask.

00:55:19.296 --> 00:55:21.882
You see, I grew up with nothing,

00:55:21.966 --> 00:55:24.385
like an orphaned child in wartime.

00:55:25.344 --> 00:55:26.345
To be honest,

00:55:27.388 --> 00:55:29.181
it still feels strange

00:55:30.516 --> 00:55:31.517
to be where I am right now.

00:55:35.563 --> 00:55:37.148
You need a thick mask

00:55:37.648 --> 00:55:40.818
to pretend like nothing's wrong.

00:55:47.867 --> 00:55:49.034
THIS FILE HAS BEEN DELETED

00:55:51.370 --> 00:55:53.164
THIS FILE HAS BEEN DELETED

00:56:00.421 --> 00:56:01.255
Found it.

00:56:01.338 --> 00:56:05.384
Man, I found it by the skin of my teeth.

00:56:06.135 --> 00:56:08.679
Another few seconds,
and this file would've been gone.

00:56:08.762 --> 00:56:10.264
It's Paek Jun-beom.

00:56:10.347 --> 00:56:12.391
So this is why he deleted everything.

00:56:12.474 --> 00:56:14.977
This bastard is so calculating.

00:56:15.060 --> 00:56:16.770
He's one scary man.

00:56:16.854 --> 00:56:18.480
What a bastard.

00:56:22.026 --> 00:56:23.402
Why don't you…

00:56:25.029 --> 00:56:27.281
take off that mask now?

00:56:33.037 --> 00:56:34.079
Who exactly are you?

00:56:35.414 --> 00:56:37.166
Why did you approach me

00:56:37.249 --> 00:56:39.293
when you knew Su-ho?

00:57:04.526 --> 00:57:07.238
Do you think I blame you…

00:57:09.323 --> 00:57:10.658
for Su-ho's death?

00:57:17.873 --> 00:57:19.124
Or do you think…

00:57:29.426 --> 00:57:31.303
I'm getting revenge for him?

00:57:41.438 --> 00:57:42.940
-She's in danger.
-What?

00:57:43.691 --> 00:57:44.650
Sir!

00:58:04.128 --> 00:58:07.339
SPECIAL THANKS TO KIM DONGJUN
FOR HIS APPEARANCE

00:58:30.738 --> 00:58:32.281
It doesn't make sense.

00:58:32.364 --> 00:58:34.533
Even if this is a revenge
on Su-ho's behalf,

00:58:34.616 --> 00:58:36.368
it's way too extreme.

00:58:36.869 --> 00:58:38.871
It's similar to my sister's accident.

00:58:38.954 --> 00:58:42.541
Criminals rely on familiar tactics
and tend to repeat what's worked before.

00:58:42.624 --> 00:58:46.045
I'm also chasing the person
who ruined my life.

00:58:46.128 --> 00:58:47.796
Let's uncover

00:58:48.339 --> 00:58:50.924
the hidden truth together.

00:58:51.008 --> 00:58:54.553
Isn't there something
you really want to say to me?

00:58:55.012 --> 00:58:58.098
Now we can finally find out
what Paek Jun-beom was trying to hide.

00:58:58.182 --> 00:58:59.266
Let go of me!

00:58:59.350 --> 00:59:01.185
It's finally come to this.

00:59:02.686 --> 00:59:04.688
Subtitle: Jenny Kim